        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I just wanted to use Zend_File for a new project, and discovered a serious bug. After submitting a file, and if the validation of some other field fails, Zend_File adds the filename with number \"0\" as attribute name to the view helper, which then looks like this:\n\n{code}\n<input type=\"file\" name=\"grf_file\" id=\"grf_file\" 0=\"OpenGFX_-_newIndustries_v0.5.grf\" \/>\n{code}\n\nThis doesn't really matter for HTML sites, but for XHTML the browser stops with a \"not well-formed XML\" message. Hence I consider this as a blocker."
        },
