        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26402",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Do you use the file-view helper ?\nBecause this helper does not display the value of the element.\n\nThe reason for this problem is not the file component but the ViewHelper.\nI was forced to add getValue to the form element because the form can not handle elements without value.\nBut the file element does not have a value in HTML.\n\nI expect that you get the above output when you don't use the proper view helper or decorator.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-14T02:28:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-14T02:28:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26403",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Here is the controller which creates the form and the class subclassing Zend_Form for decorators.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-14T03:38:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-14T03:38:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26404",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Is there a reason why you erased the file validator from the file element ?\nlines 77-98 in your form\n\nThis prevents the file element from being rendered correct because you erased the file decorator which is attached per default.\n\nYou would have the same problem when you add a image and delete the image decorator from the image element.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-14T05:45:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-14T05:45:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26407",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Indeed that was it, exchainging the ViewHelper decorator with the File decorator for the File element fixed it. Probably this should be mentioned either in the docs that the Form_Element_File needs the File instead of the ViewHelper decorator, or even better let the File element see, if a ViewHelepr decorator was added, and automatically exchange it either with the File decorator or throw an exception.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-14T06:48:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-14T06:48:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26413",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It is not possible to throw an exception.\nThe user must be able to give a own implementation of a file decorator.\n\nThe documentation mentions the file decorator.\n\nIt is only needed in some special cases.\n\n* When you use XHTML\n* When you use Subforms\n* When you use MultiFiles\n\nA request to the author of Zend_Form regarding the problem of setDecorator for File, Images and other elements was until now not answered",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-15T01:14:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-15T01:14:56.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
